goals.question: What is the most common terrain type in the dataset?

goals.rationale: This will help us understand the distribution of terrain types in the dataset and if there are any imbalances or biases.

goals.question: Is there a correlation between lumosity and saturation values?

goals.rationale: This will help us understand if there is any relationship between lumosity and saturation values and if they tend to vary together or independently.

goals.question: How does the distribution of terrain coordinates vary across the dataset?

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='lumosity')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of lumosity values across all terrain types?', wrap=True)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = sns.boxplot(x='name', y='saturation', data=data)
    plt.title('How does saturation vary across different terrain types?', wrap=True)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    terrain_counts = data['name'].value_counts()
    sns.barplot(x=terrain_counts.index, y=terrain_counts.values)
    plt.xlabel('Terrain Type')
    plt.ylabel('Count')

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
